blicProfile?language=EN>FallenDeity Decandidus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/4/01 10:17:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Tears of Druzzil..    kinda Po'd</span><hr size=1> Checked my born on date yesterday.. 11/5/00..   Ever since day 1, I've been looking at the spells from well, lvl 1 to lvl 60... Now im finally getting some of the spells that were such great eye candy on paper, and well, I'm pissed. <br>
<br>
The thing that really killed me today, when i finally dinged 52, and a guildy got me my third copy of Tears of Druzzil (damn near the same time, maybe a 15 min gap) I decided what the hell, Ill scribe this one instead of giving it to that bastard Erud for my 6th copy of Abscond. I wanted to test it out asap, before coming to work and I only have about 10 mins.. (I WAS really excited thinking that this spell would be something nice to use in Seb if the mobs were split up enough) <br>
<br>
One of my guildies, a necro was at the GF spires and asked for a taxi, so out I come to pick him up, but ask him where he is bound and if I can try a nice little new spell on him before I port him. He says not on me, but on the pet, and we laughed a bit. Anyways, hes lvl 43, Again, Im 52. His pet was well beyond green to me. We start our duel, I use the old lvl 4 root on his pet, then slap him with ToD. I get this:<br>
<br>
Resisted<br>
<br>
600DD - Root broke.<br>
<br>
He pulled his pet back and then i started over.<br>
<br>
600DD<br>
<br>
Resisted<br>
<br>
Resisted - Root broke..<br>
<br>
SO... Wtf?!? Are all the tears spells so lousy that they can be resisted by something, what... 15 lvls lower than you? <br>
<br>
-FallenDeity Decandidus-<br>
/slapping Poe i nthe face.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ullith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/4/01 10:30:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tears of Druzzil..    kinda Po'd</span><hr size=1> Take my word for it. That spell is one of the best you get, especially at that level. When in a group wait till the single mob has sustained decent damage then let loose. So long as at least 2 waves hit (They usually do) you have a better mana effecient spell than ice comet. If all 3 hit which is pretty often you have the most damage for mana you can get at that level. I use the spell constantly when grouped and it quickly became my favorite damage spell. <p>Llith Rosethorn, Disgruntled Taxi Driver of 52nd street</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufallendeitydecandidus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FallenDeity Decandidus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/4/01 10:39:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tears of Druzzil..    kinda Po'd</span><hr size=1> Thats what I was thinking before I casted it.. Wtf is up with a lvl sub40 pet resisting it though??? /shrug <br>
<br>
-FallenDeity Decandidus-<br>
-tired as hell and remembering a bad exp with a green shaman pet (unrootable bastard!) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufallendeitydecandidus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FallenDeity Decandidus</A> at: 6/4/01 11:02:11 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uasiago.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Asiago</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/4/01 10:41:30 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.spacehotel.com/images/asi2Icon.jpg width=224 height=175></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tears of Druzzil..    kinda Po'd</span><hr size=1> For some reason the Tears line doesn't ever land the killing blow (except if you nuke yourself so I hear).  If your target has less than 600 hp left it will resist any more waves of the nuke.  The rains also seem to get resisted more often that nukes as well but on single target mobs with medium or low resist (sebilis upstairs, plane of fear, etc) you can usually land better than 2/3 on average.<br>
<br>
Asiago <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aeben>Aeben</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/4/01 11:12:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> Tears of Druzzil = raid exp.<br>
<br>
Used it all day on giants in the Kael arena area.  As long as the rest of your group doesn't totally suck, you can ks groups with Ragebringers and not die.<br>
<br>
The resists are kinda funky on rains in general (ToD is magic based...unless they messed up the icon).  Sometimes you're the nail, but sometimes you can really hammer the s*** out of stuff and not get aggro.<br>
<br>
I would chain cast this and lava storm and do up to 6k damage on a single mob (I don't think the ones we were fighting had over 20k hps) and never heard my name once.<br>
<br>
For a finishing touch, you can cast a draught right after the rain and it will hit right as the last wave of the rain does, giving you 2450ish dmg in ~10 seconds (start to finish, without aggroing) for ~600 mana.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uodaend.showPublicProfile?language=EN>OdaenD</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 12:08:59 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.ashenvendetta.com/odaen/odaen_icon.gif border=0></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tears of Druzzil..    kinda Po'd</span><hr size=1> The resist rates on the entire Tears line of spells sux, if you don't have a shaman/chanter debuffing the mobs.  At the very least, use your staff of temp flux on mobs that you will use solusek or prexus on.  But even then, at times mobs are so MR, that your staff won't even touch them.<br>
When they land, oh baby.  When they don't, I wanna chuck my keyboard across the den. <p><blockquote>
<p align="left"> </p>
<P align="left"><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=64589">Odaen</a><BR>
<p align="left"><img border="0" src="Http://www.ashenvendetta.com/odaen/Odaen_sig.gif" width="201" height="62"></p>


</blockquote>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucabottp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CabotTP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 1:35:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tears of Druzzil..    kinda Po'd</span><hr size=1> <br>
The only real &quot;problem&quot; I have with Tears is you can't really use it around an enchanter mezzing.  However, there's some nice places where mobs can't be mezzed, and then Tears owns.<br>
<br>
The number one place I cast Tears: Kael raids.  We have a very good FD puller (hi Monica) so we often get single pulls, and the occasional extra gets charmed.  No real issues for using Tears here.<br>
<br>
As far as damage efficiency... it's better than draught.  The &quot;norm&quot; for me is to get 2 full hits and 1 full resist.  When it hits 2/3 like this, it has slightly better dmg/mana than draught, and I get more med time that I would casting 3 draughts.  When it gets 3/3 hits, the ratio is even better.<br>
<br>
In conclusion, I love my Tears <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><BR>Cabot Coriolis of Tholuxe Paells<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=yueamin>Yueamin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 1:58:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tears of Druzzil..    kinda Po'd</span><hr size=1> I dont have much experience with this spell yet,just got it the other day.The first time i tried it out, all  three waves hit and root didnt break. I couldnt belive it, i thought that maybe just maybe, this rain spell would be good. But after using it another 10 times, i realized it pretty much sucks. I can see its potential in certain situations = mobs with low mr and high hp :P hmm do those exist??  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucassiusruneblaze.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cassius Runeblaze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 2:31:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tears of Druzzil..    kinda Po'd</span><hr size=1> <br>
I use this spell a lot, but I honestly wonder if I parsed my logs, would it really be mana efficient <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Its definitely border line as 1-2 resists is defintely a lot more common that no resists...<br>
<br>
If they fixed resists on this line through the level range, I'd definitely be grateful. My personal feeling is that if you are using a rain of the type the mob shuld be susceptible to, each wave should have a 95% chance of hitting if the mob isnt higher level or whatever...<br>
<br>
...then again you could say the same for all wizzie spells. Personally, I have a sneaking suspician that when they do dmg comps between the classes, they have a slightly idealistic idea of how much resists impact things. I'm so used to it that I don't blink any more, but it seems ridiculous if you step back and look at it. <p>Cassius Runeblaze &lt;Avatars of Discord&gt;<BR>
lvl 55<BR>
Rodcet</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aeben>Aeben</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 2:31:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I can see its potential in certain situations = mobs with low mr and high hp :P hmm do those exist??<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
hail a protector of Zek<br>
<br>
Just an example...at 53, I would often land all 3 waves on those bad boys.  Those are the ones I'm talking about where I could get in 6k+ damage and no aggro.  We had 3 groups, so they didn't last long enough to do more than that...<br>
<br>
They may be few and far between, but high level, low MR mobs do exist. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aennyilofkarana>Aennyil of Karana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 3:11:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tears of Druzzil..    kinda Po'd</span><hr size=1> Actually, you can get a kill with tears IF it is hitting more than one target. Also I've noticed I'm getting 4 waves total instead of the three I seem to recall hearing about if the rain is hitting two targets. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umihos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mihos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 3:19:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tears of Druzzil..    kinda Po'd</span><hr size=1> The tears line is by far my favorite line of spells.  It just takes alot of practice to know when to use them.  I do wish the resists where just a tad less though.<br>
<br>
Mihos <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwizban.showPublicProfile?language=EN>wizban</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 3:22:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tears of Druzzil..    kinda Po'd</span><hr size=1> This spell is awesome , I was going back to back with a Magi also using Rain in Chardok the other night we were demolition team <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Great fun especially if you have a de buffer...<br>
<br>
:P)<br>
<br>
Wiz<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Level 55th Evoker of Cazic Thule
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aeben>Aeben</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 3:25:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> There's not too many times when you want to hit more than one target with a rain.  And I have seen similar things, but I think if you look closely, you only did damage 3 times.<br>
<br>
1st wave<br>
Hit target00 for 600<br>
target01 resisted<br>
<br>
2nd wave<br>
Hit target00 for 600<br>
Hit target01 for 600<br>
<br>
...something like that.<br>
<br>
But, if you're hitting 2 targets, you'd better be damn sure there's tanks on both, or you're in a world of hurt.<br>
<br>
Really though, for 2-4 targets (assuming you actually want to hit them all), you'd be better off using a pillar.  Resist rates on them are much lower.  The AoE seems to be about the same.  Mana efficiency for 2 targets is similar, and favors the pillar quite a bit for 3 or 4. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ueanaminelessedil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eanamin Elessedil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 3:30:51 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.winternet.com/~mikelr/assets/Freudian.jpg height=75 width=75></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tears of Druzzil..    kinda Po'd</span><hr size=1> Yeah... all rain spells will do a maximum of 4 &quot;hits&quot; of damage in a maximum of 3 waves, but only a maximum of 3 hits to any given target.<br>
<br>
1 target = 3 waves : 3 hits<br>
2 targets = 2 waves each target : 4 hits<br>
3 targets = 2 waves, 3 targets take 1 wave, 1 target takes 2 : 4 hits<br>
4 targets = 1 wave, 4 targets take 1 wave each : 4 hits<br>
<br>
One time in the arena I saw 1 rain spell (edit: it was Tears of Druzzil) hit 6 times (multiple targets, 2 waves, totalled 6 hits).  I can't explain that... I don't duel a whole lot and I play on a blue server, so I'm not sure if that's a regular occurance or just a bizarre fluke.  I was just crashing the party, and was probably almost as shocked by the 6 hits from the spell as they were <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ueanaminelessedil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eanamin Elessedil</A> at: 6/5/01 3:37:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uauroreakengro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aurore Akengro</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 5:01:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tears of Druzzil..    kinda Po'd</span><hr size=1> All AE spells (pillars, tears, etc) hit UNLIMITED targets in PvP. That's one reason why NPCs use Al'Kabor spells: They don't have a target limit on them, and will hit ALL the PCs that are in the radius of the spell.<br>
<br>
Oh the life of a wizard NPC... <p>Aurore
