</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 7:21:52 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tears of Druzzil..    kinda Po'd</span><hr size=1> The rain spells are too resisted still, yes, that's one problem with them.  Resistances across the board are a problem, though, I'd reduce them from level 1-60 for Wizards on DD spells but that's not how Verant sees things. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg" ></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujonjayelvenstar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jonjay Elvenstar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalRainbow.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 7:32:01 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/edit/raw/image/12/4130312.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tears of Druzzil..    kinda Po'd</span><hr size=1> This spell and the upgrade Tears of Solusek ROX.<br>
This spell is a situation spell.<br>
<br>
Get a Druid with Ro's Fiery Sundering (-40 FR) and this will do 1800 DMG 2 of 3 times.  And Solusek will get you 1950.<br>
<br>
Clearing Dhall Frogs in Sebilis with this is laughable.  Mages get this spell with a different name a couple levels up, so there is justice there.  <br>
<br>
As to root breaking - of course:  It will always break with attack on the mob.  <br>
<br>
Wizards are effective if you are creative and use what is given you.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uigronimus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>igronimus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 7:36:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tears of Druzzil..    kinda Po'd</span><hr size=1> This spell rules, I use it all the time, specially in XP grouping situations.  It actually allows us to operate at a level of mana efficiency where we can make a worthwile contribution to a group.<br>
<br>
In xp group situations, if there's multiple mobs I use my regular single targets till you're down to one mob and don't have to worry about breaking mez.  On the last mob of if it's a single pull, I wait till the tanks beat it down to about 75% and start raining.  Usually at least get 2 waves for full, which makes it more efficient than draught and if you get 3 waves, it's way more efficient than draught.   A lot of times I'll dump tishan's discord on it right after I cast to make sure even if it aggroes its still stuck for the 3rd wave.  Even on raids if you have some decent debuffers, these spells will hit whites and yellows pretty well.  Just be careful, though against big mobs on raids.  I've been summoned into my own rain spells quite a few times.  It was quite embarassing one time when the message &quot;Igronimus has been slain by Igronimus&quot; came across everyone's screen.<br>
<br>
Just a word to the skeptics out there, the rain spells are one of the few spells that puts us on a level playing field in regular grouping situations, so before you toss it to the back of your spell book, you ought to test it out thoroughly, you'll prolly find you really like it. <p><hr>
<font size=+1><b>
Igronimus von Gnomus
</b></font><br>
<i>52nd Level Wizard</i><br>
<i>Clan Impact - Innoruuk</i>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubethude.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bethude</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 7:50:36 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tears of Druzzil..    kinda Po'd</span><hr size=1> At your level, only two waves have to hit to get higher efficiency than draught of fire.  As a mob gets lower on hp, the greater the resists for rains spells.  That skele pet probably had about 1200 hp and therefore your chance of getting resisted skyrocketed as the second and third waves came in.  You'll find that the spell works much better on mobs with 6k+ hp since you have much more leeway on casting it while the mob still has a lot of hp but still doesn't aggro on you.  Of course, having a chanter tash the mob is good too.<br>
<br>
Since the efficiency of the post 50 rain spells remains constant and the draughts get better, you will find that at 57 you're pretty much always better off using draught of ice. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaeanorendarion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeanor Endarion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/picon.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 8:23:14 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/ppic.jpg height=200 width=152></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tears of Druzzil..    kinda Po'd</span><hr size=1> Let's not forget he was casting on a pet in a duel situation - I believe PVP rules apply: higher resist, lower damage. <p><b>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe</b></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=4050.topic&start=21&stop=28>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=4107.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=4109.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=4050.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http: